From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PlazaMC <dev@plazamc.org>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 22:30:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Load deferred folder worlds without Slime override

Configured ANVIL/LINEAR worlds defer their loading until Bukkit world
creation is possible. Previously the deferred load only ran from the Slime
overworld override path, so with a non-SLIME default format those worlds
never loaded. Call loadDeferredFolderWorlds after loadInitialWorlds as well;
it is a no-op when the Slime path already consumed the list.

diff --git a/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java b/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
index 5717b4a..0c4f0c4 100644
--- a/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
+++ b/net/minecraft/server/MinecraftServer.java
@@ -605,6 +605,7 @@ public abstract class MinecraftServer extends ReentrantBlockableEventLoop<TickTa
         io.papermc.paper.world.PaperWorldLoader loader = io.papermc.paper.world.PaperWorldLoader.create(this, levelId);
         org.plazamc.server.slime.PlazaSlimeWorldBootstrap.bootstrapDefaultWorlds(this); // Plaza - Slime World default bootstrap
         loader.loadInitialWorlds();
+        org.plazamc.server.world.PlazaWorldManager.loadDeferredFolderWorlds(); // Plaza - load folder worlds deferred during bootstrap when the Slime override path did not run
         // Paper end - rework world loading process
         if (profiledDuration != null) {
             profiledDuration.finish(true);
